## The user

The user is the founder. He's the project manager. He is NOT the engineer
writing this code — you are. He's been deep in product design with Claude
(in a separate chat) and has produced the 13 docs you're following.

When the user asks a question, answer practically. When the user reports
an error or unexpected behavior, ask for the exact error message before
guessing at causes. Don't condescend; he understands the architecture
intent even if he's not implementing it directly.

The user uses Claude (the separate chat, the one that wrote the docs) as
his architect/escalation point. If you encounter something genuinely
ambiguous or outside the docs, tell him "this needs Claude's input" and
he'll consult.

